This package is currently maintained by Bill Teahan (wjt@informatics.bangor.ac.uk)


1. To install:
	a. "make config"
	b. edit CONFIG and change the compiler options to your configuration
	c. "make"

2. To build the default models use:
	"make train"

3. For a simple demo:
	"make demo"

   otherwise cd into apps/*, and "make demo" in a couple of them.

4. To create a new version.
	a. Copy everything to new home directory.
	b. Edit Makefile and increment or change VERSION.
	c. Type "make config".
	d. Check CONFIG has the correct Home directory.

5. If there are problems, try to fix them, then let me know.
   :-)



